⚠️ COMMON PITFALLS

17). What to Avoid

-code(

❌ DON'T: Forget to handle non-scene messages

bot.on(:message) do |ctx|
if ctx.current_scene
# Scene will handle it
else
ctx.reply("I don't understand")
end
end

❌ DON'T: Create infinite loops

step :danger do |ctx|
ctx.reply("Looping...")

Don't call the same step without condition!

ctx.current_scene.process_step(ctx, :danger)  # INFINITE LOOP!
end

✅ DO: Add exit conditions

step :safe do |ctx|
if ctx.session[:count].to_i < 5
ctx.session[:count] = ctx.session[:count].to_i + 1
ctx.reply("Count: #{ctx.session[:count]}")
# Stay in same step
else
ctx.reply("Done!")
ctx.leave_scene
end
end
)

🎯 BEST PRACTICES

18). Scene Design Tips

-note(1. Keep scenes focused - One scene = one complete workflow)
-note(2. Use session for persistence - Data survives between steps)
-note(3. Use state for temporaries - Data only for current step)
-note(4. Always have exit path - Users can cancel anytime)
-note(5. Validate inputs - Check data in each step)
-note(6. Add timeouts - Prevent abandoned scenes)
-note(7. Log scene activity - Debugging is easier)
-note(8. Test with real users - Scenes are UX-heavy)

19). Scene Lifecycle

```
┌─────────────────────┐
│   ctx.enter_scene   │
│        ↓            │
│    on_enter hook    │
│        ↓            │
│   First step runs   │
│        ↓            │
│   User responds     │
│        ↓            │
│   Next step runs    │
│        ↓            │
│   (Repeat...)       │
│        ↓            │
│   ctx.leave_scene   │
│        ↓            │
│    on_leave hook    │
└─────────────────────┘
```

🚀 NEXT LEVEL SCENES

20). Dynamic Scene Generation

-code(

Create scenes on the fly

def create_dynamic_scene(user_id, steps)
scene_id = "dynamic_#{user_id}_#{Time.now.to_i}"

bot.scene(scene_id.to_sym) do
steps.each_with_index do |question, index|
step "step_#{index}".to_sym do |ctx|
ctx.reply(question)
end
end

```
step :finish do |ctx|
  ctx.reply("Survey complete!")
  ctx.leave_scene
end
```

end

scene_id
end

Usage

survey_steps = [
"How was our service?",
"Rate from 1-10:",
"Any comments?"
]

scene_id = create_dynamic_scene(ctx.user_id, survey_steps)
ctx.enter_scene(scene_id.to_sym)
)

